description.narrative: UNICEF Eswatini achieved 100% of planned surveys, research studies and evaluation. These were; Situation of Children and Adolescents in Eswatini, Rapid Assessment of Grade 0 in schools in Eswatini, Open budget Survey and the Country Programme Evaluation. Recommendations of these reports informed improvements in programming including the development of the new Country Programme. Five budget analysis on National budget, Health, Education, WASH, and Social Protection were undertaken with technical support from UNICEF. These are used to advocate for improved public finance for children and adolescents next year. Consistent tracking of results achievement led to high key performance for the office. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/12/2019
